  • Method Details

    • createFeed

      public Feed createFeed​(java.lang.String name, java.lang.String description, boolean badgesEnabled, boolean hideDeletedPackageVersions) throws DefaultParametersException, java.io.IOException
      Create a feed, a container for various package types.

      Feeds can be created in a project if the project parameter is included when instantiating the class. This can be done by injecting the instance of AzDDefaultParameters with project name. If the project parameter is omitted, the feed will not be associated with a project and will be created at the organization level.

      Parameters:
      name - Provide the name of the feed
      description - Provide the description for the feed
      badgesEnabled - Enable or disable the badge in the feed. Default to false.
      hideDeletedPackageVersions - Hides the deleted package version. Default to true.
      Returns:
      For successful operation -> Feed
      Throws:
      DefaultParametersException - throws default parameter exception DefaultParametersException
      java.io.IOException - throws IO Exception exception IOException

    • createFeedView

      public FeedView createFeedView​(java.lang.String feedName, java.lang.String name, java.lang.String feedViewType, java.lang.String visibility) throws java.io.IOException, DefaultParametersException
      Create a new view on the referenced feed.

      The project parameter must be supplied if the feed was created in a project.

      Parameters:
      feedName - provide the name or id of the feed
      name - name of the feed view
      feedViewType - type of the feed view. Allowed values are [implicit and release]
      visibility - visibility of the view. Allowed values are [aadTenant, collection, organization, private]
      Returns:
      Feed view object FeedView
      Throws:
      DefaultParametersException - throws default parameter exception DefaultParametersException
      java.io.IOException - throws IO Exception exception IOException

    • deleteFeed

      public void deleteFeed​(java.lang.String feedId) throws DefaultParametersException, java.io.IOException
      Remove a feed and all its packages. The feed moves to the recycle bin and is reversible.

      The project parameter must be supplied if the feed was created in a project. If the feed is not associated with any project, omit the project parameter from the request.

      Parameters:
      feedId - Name or Id of the feed.
      Throws:
      DefaultParametersException - throws default parameter exception DefaultParametersException
      java.io.IOException - throws IO Exception exception IOException

    • getFeedPermissions

      public FeedPermissions getFeedPermissions​(java.lang.String feedName, boolean excludeInheritedPermissions, java.lang.String identityDescriptor, boolean includeDeletedFeeds, boolean includeIds) throws DefaultParametersException, java.io.IOException
      Get the permissions for a feed.

      The project parameter must be supplied if the feed was created in a project. If the feed is not associated with any project, omit the project parameter from the request.

      Parameters:
      feedName - Name or Id of the feed.
      excludeInheritedPermissions - True to only return explicitly set permissions on the feed. Default is false.
      identityDescriptor - Filter permissions to the provided identity.
      includeDeletedFeeds - If includeDeletedFeeds is true, then feedId must be specified by name and not by Guid.
      includeIds - True to include user Ids in the response. Default is false.
      Returns:
      Feed Permissions FeedPermissions
      Throws:
      DefaultParametersException - throws default parameter exception DefaultParametersException
      java.io.IOException - throws IO Exception exception IOException

    • getFeeds

      public Feeds getFeeds() throws DefaultParametersException, java.io.IOException
      Get all feeds in an account where you have the provided role access.

      If the project parameter is present, gets all feeds in the given project. If omitted, gets all feeds in the organization.

      Returns:
      array of feeds Feeds
      Throws:
      DefaultParametersException - throws default parameter exception DefaultParametersException
      java.io.IOException - throws IO Exception exception IOException

    • getFeeds

      public Feeds getFeeds​(java.lang.String feedRole, boolean includeDeletedUpstreams, boolean includeUrls) throws DefaultParametersException, java.io.IOException
      Get all feeds in an account where you have the provided role access.

      If the project parameter is present, gets all feeds in the given project. If omitted, gets all feeds in the organization.

      Parameters:
      feedRole - Filter by this role, either Administrator(4), Contributor(3), or Reader(2) level permissions.
      includeDeletedUpstreams - Include upstreams that have been deleted in the response.
      includeUrls - Resolve names if true
      Returns:
      array of feeds Feeds
      Throws:
      DefaultParametersException - throws default parameter exception DefaultParametersException
      java.io.IOException - throws IO Exception exception IOException

    • setFeedPermissions

      public FeedPermissions setFeedPermissions​(java.lang.String feedName, java.lang.String displayName, java.lang.String identityDescriptor, boolean isInheritedRole, java.lang.String role) throws DefaultParametersException, java.io.IOException
      Update the permissions on a feed.

      The project parameter must be supplied if the feed was created in a project. If the feed is not associated with any project, omit the project parameter from the request.

      Parameters:
      feedName - Name or Id of the feed.
      displayName - Display name for the identity. This can be an empty string or null
      identityDescriptor - Identity associated with this role. You can run getFeedPermissions to get the Identity descriptor
      isInheritedRole - Boolean indicating whether the role is inherited or set directly.
      role - The role for this identity on a feed.
      Returns:
      array of feed permissions FeedPermissions
      Throws:
      DefaultParametersException - throws default parameter exception DefaultParametersException

      java.io.IOException

    • updateFeed

      public Feed updateFeed​(java.lang.String feedName, boolean badgesEnabled, java.lang.String description, boolean hideDeletedPackageVersions, boolean upstreamEnabled) throws DefaultParametersException, java.io.IOException
      Change the attributes of a feed.

      The project parameter must be supplied if the feed was created in a project. If the feed is not associated with any project, omit the project parameter from the request.

      Parameters:
      feedName - Name or Id of the feed.
      badgesEnabled - If set, this feed supports generation of package badges.
      description - A description for the feed.
      hideDeletedPackageVersions - If set, feed will hide all deleted/unpublished versions
      upstreamEnabled - If set, the feed can proxy packages from an upstream feed
      Returns:
      feed Feed
      Throws:
      DefaultParametersException - throws default parameter exception DefaultParametersException
      com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException - --> JsonProcessingException
      java.io.IOException
